post_text:
4/3/20
This is Steve Dionisio Superintendent of Charlotte County Schools.
I am calling with a message for staff, parents and students
As we conclude our first week of online learning, I just want to thank all of you for your patience and resilience.
I am so proud of the way all of you have worked together to make sure learning continues in Charlotte County.
I realize it has not always been smooth or easy but you have continued to work through all obstacles as a team.
I would also like to send out a special thank you to employees from CHAMPS showing up every day to prepare and pass out food to our kids.
Simply Incredible.

Again thank you in advance for your continued patience and cooperation.

Please Stay home and have a great weekend.

post_text:
3/30/20
This is Steve Dionisio Superintendent of Schools.
I am calling with an update for staff and parents
The Commissioner of Education has instructed School Districts that schools will now remain closed until May 1st instead of the original date of April 15.
Again, the Instructional Continuity Plan that began today will now remain in effect until at least May 1st instead of the original date of April 15.

Thank you in advance for your continued patience as information become available I will get it to you.

Thank you

post_text:
Charlotte County Public Schools continues to work with the Charlotte County Emergency Operation Center and closely monitor the approach of Hurricane Dorian.

Charlotte County Schools will have school on Tuesday. Any activities scheduled for Tuesday can proceed as scheduled.

Reminder the three Year Round Schools do not have school tomorrow per their schedule and that does not change.

Please continue to monitor the storm and the CCPS Website for any additional updates.

post_text:
Charlotte County Public Schools is continuing to work with the Charlotte County Emergency Operation Center and closely monitor the approach of the still extremely slow moving Hurricane Dorian.

Although all indications call for a turn to happen with this powerful storm, unfortunately, it has not happened just yet so we are holding off on a decision about school on Tuesday until tomorrow.

We will make any announcements about school closing tomorrow as, even if the storm does turn, we could still see tropical storm force winds depending how far inland the storm comes.

We will let everyone know the decision as early as possible tomorrow.

We will continue to use the parent connect system as well as continuing to place the information on our website to keep you informed.

In addition, a reminder that we will also notify local news media of any cancelations.

Stay safe.

post_text:
Charlotte County Public Schools is continuing to work with the Charlotte County Emergency Operation Center and closely monitor the approach of Hurricane Dorian. Although the track has improved for Charlotte County, we will continue to monitor the storm and I implore you to do the same.

We will make an announcement on school closings on Sunday. All announcements will be made via the Parent Connect phone system, the CCPS Website, and local news media.

Please continue to monitor the CCPS website for updates.

Stay Safe.
